HEADWORD: Fuze plug
<hw>Fuze plug</hw> }</mhw>.
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Ordnance)</fld> <def>A plug fitted to the fuse hole of
a shell to hold the fuse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fusible plug that screws into a receptacle, used
as a fuse in electric wiring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fusibility</ent>⟦br⟧
